cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.SY

The paper discusses the hardware implementation of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) using Stochastic Computing (SC). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) as it deals with the design and optimization of hardware for specific applications. The paper also focuses on image classification tasks using DCNNs, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of SC for highly scalable and parallel hardware implementation, which is related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Finally, the paper proposes accurate activation designs for SC-based neurons, which can be considered as a control system design, and hence related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
